*EDIT: Fixed, realized I have to specify the use of checkboxes in the second example, thank you Evelynn! ///* Hello everyone - I have a very strange situation happening with HubSpot forms and the <https://legacydocs.HubSpot.com/docs/methods/forms/advanced_form_options|form embed /forms API>.
We have used the form embed customization plenty of times with our clients to help route form submissions to different pages based off a submission's answers _(so for example, if someone fills out a form and chooses California for their state, upon form submission they would redirect to a specific meeting link)_

However, recently, the code doesn't work anymore for new forms created. At least from what I can tell. I have been pulling out my hair over this and was advised to reach out here. I am using essentially the same working code on a different form, but it's not working :sob:  Any advice would be appreciated. Did anything change with the forms API I am not aware of? These are all contact properties btw.

Here's some examples -

Form #1 - Works fine - <https://www.harvestroi.com/test-2> (redirects based off answer for b2b,b2c etc)
Code -
``` <script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/embed/v2.js"></script>
<script>
  hbspt.forms.create({
   region: "na1",
  portalId: "PORTALID",
  formId: "FORMID",
  onFormSubmit: function($form) {
    var favouriteFruit = $form.find('select[name="b2b_or_b2c"]').val();

    setTimeout( function() {
      if ( favouriteFruit == "B2B (business to business)" ) {
        window.location.href = "<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pineapple>";
      }       
      if ( favouriteFruit == "B2C (business to consumer)" ) {
        window.location.href = "<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banana>";
      }      
      if ( favouriteFruit == "Both" ) {
        window.location.href = "<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grape>";
      }
      if ( favouriteFruit == "Niether" ) {
        window.location.href = "<https://en.wikipedia.org/>";
      }

    }, 500 ); // Waits 1/2 second to redirect.
  }
});
</script>  ```
Form #2 - Does NOT work, essentially has the same code though !? (link) <https://www.harvestroi.com/test> (supposed to redirect to different pages for small business owner and deal service providers)
